                            <comment id="14474032" author="blackdrag" created="Thu, 21 Feb 2013 12:27:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;shouldn&apos;t the loader for the source unit be used here?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14474076" author="werdna" created="Fri, 22 Feb 2013 13:12:27 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;shouldn&apos;t the loader for the source unit be used here?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Probably.  I&apos;d be fine with that.  I just know that what we have now breaks greclipse.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, found two more suspicious {{Class.forName}}s.  They may be problematic for greclipse:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;in &lt;tt&gt;org.codehaus.groovy.transform.stc.GroovyTypeCheckingExtensionSupport.TypeCheckingDSL.invokeMethod(String, Object)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;in &lt;tt&gt;org.codehaus.groovy.transform.ASTTransformationVisitor.doAddGlobalTransforms(ASTTransformationsContext, boolean)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14474219" author="melix" created="Wed, 6 Mar 2013 04:10:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think Jochen is right, in general I don&apos;t think it&apos;s a good idea to use the context classloader. I need to change the codec so that it takes the source unit class loader as a constructor arg, then use it. In TypeCheckingDSL, it&apos;s used to load AST node classes, I think this is less of an issue since they are only groovy core classes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do you think Andrew? Would using the SU classloader be ok for you?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14474184" author="werdna" created="Wed, 6 Mar 2013 09:44:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d be fine with using the sourceunit&apos;s loader.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
